cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new fully convolutional model, which involves the use of a `Slave' network and a `Master' network, indicating that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of skip connections, which are commonly used in neural networks, indicating that it may also fall under the sub-categories of cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) and cs.CL (computation and language).
